definition.value: A dTDP-sugar having 3-amino-3,4,6-trideoxy-D-glucose as the sugar component.
A member of the class of  acetamides that is the acetyl derivative of 6-amino-2-oxohexanoic acid.
A plastoquinone in which the number of isoprene units in the side chain is 9.
The (R)-enantiomer of 3-methyl-2-oxovaleric acid.

Any member of a group of fat-soluble 2-methyl-1,4-napthoquinones that exhibit biological activity against vitamin K deficiency. Vitamin K is required for the synthesis of prothrombin and certain other blood coagulation factors.
An altrose that has D- configuration.
A primary alcohol being cinnamyl alcohol hydroxylated at C-4 of the phenyl ring.
An unsaturated fatty acyl-CoA that results from the formal condensation of the thiol group of coenzyme A with the carboxy group of (2-trans,6-cis)-dodeca-2,6-dienoic acid.
A non-proteinogenc alpha-amino acid that is alanine in which one of the hydrogens of the terminal methyl group has been replaced by a dihydroxy(oxido)-lambda(5)-phosphanyl group.
A dipeptide consisting of a modified L-proline residue attached to glycine via a peptide linkage.
A 2-amino-2-deoxy-D-glucopyranose that is D-glucosamine having a beta-configuration at the anomeric position.
A dicarboxylic acid that is butenedioic acid in which the hydrogen at the 2-position is substituted by a hydroxy group.
A digalactosylglycerol derivative in which the digalactosyl moiety is alpha-D-galactosyl-(1->6)-beta-D-galactosyl at O-3, with O-1 and O-2 both acylated.
L-Proline in which a hydrogen at the 4-position of the pyrrolidine ring is substituted by a hydroxy group (S-configuration).
A dialkyl ketone that is a four-carbon ketone carrying a single keto- group at position C-2.
A scyllo-inositol phosphate that is 1D-3-amino-1-guanidino-1,3-dideoxy-scyllo-inositol carrying a single phospho substituent at position 6.
A purine ribonucleoside 5'-tetraphosphate compound having 5'-xanthosyl residues at the P(1)- and P(4)-positions.
A member of the class of tetracyclines that is anhydrotetracycline in which the dimethylamino group at position 4 has been replaced by a keto group.
An ultra-long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is triacontane in which one of the terminal methyl hydrogens is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A organochlorine compound that is  4,4'-dichlorodiphenylmethane in which one of the methylene hydrogens is replaced by a hydroxymethyl group.
A tetrahydroxyflavanone that is flavanone substituted by hydroxy groups at positions 5, 7, 3' and 4' respectively.
A very long-chain primary fatty alcohol that is hexacosane in which a hydrogen attached to one of the terminal carbons is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A hydroxyimidazole that is 5-hydroxyimidazole in which the hydrogen at position 4 is replaced by a carboxymethyl group.
